# Lab Environment Overview

> **Before you begin**, locate your **Student Number** in the **Environment Information** pane on the right-hand side of your lab interface. All credentials and identities used throughout this lab are tied to that number.

***

## Your Lab Credentials

Your lab credentials are linked directly to your assigned student number.

| Purpose | Format | Example (Student 1) |
|---|---|---|
| Netskope Tenant Admin Login | `student{N}@netskope.com` | `student1@netskope.com` |
| Real-Time Policy / Netskope Client Identity | `student{N}@nsci-training.com` | `student1@nsci-training.com` |

***

## Understanding Your Identities

### 1. Netskope Tenant — Admin Access

When logging in to the **Netskope tenant** as an administrator, use your student email in the following format:

```
student{N}@netskope.com
```

For example, if you are **Student 1**, your admin login would be:

```
student1@netskope.com
```

***

### 2. Real-Time Policy Testing & Netskope Client

When **configuring Real-Time Policies** and performing tests, you will be identified by your `@nsci-training.com` email address. This is also the identity registered on the **Netskope Client** installed on your lab machine.

```
student{N}@nsci-training.com
```

For example, if you are **Student 1**, your identity during policy testing would be:

```
student1@nsci-training.com
```

> **Note:** Replace `{N}` with your actual student number throughout all lab exercises.
